# When to use

Mention this rule (for example `@305-pr-description-authoring`) when you want a **paste-ready PR body** or **pre-merge checklist** for **this repository** (ai-config-os): opening a PR, filling GitHub/GitLab description fields, or generating markdown the mergeability gate expects.

Related skills: `shared/skills/pr-description/SKILL.md`, `shared/skills/commit-conventions/SKILL.md`.

## Required behaviour

1. **Read first**: If you have filesystem access, read `shared/skills/pr-description/templates/pr-body-default.md` and follow its **exact** section order, `##` / `###` headings, checklist lines, and final **CI Status** paragraph. Do not invent a shorter outline.

2. **Fill, do not echo placeholders**: Replace placeholder lines (for example “Brief description of what this PR does.”) with real content. Mark `[x]` only for items you can confirm; use `[ ]` otherwise and add short `— N/A` where a line does not apply.

3. **Opt-out only by request**: Do not replace this structure with a bullet-only summary unless the user **explicitly** asks for a different format or a minimal outline.

4. **Title**: Keep &lt;70 characters; use Conventional Commits (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, etc.) per `commit-conventions`.

## Trigger pattern

```text
@305-pr-description-authoring
Task: Draft PR description for my branch
Context: <summary of changes, or point to commits>
```

If the rule is not invoked, still prefer the same template whenever the user asks for a **PR description** or **PR body** for **ai-config-os** in this workspace.
